summary:
Robert Njathika is a researcher, and cultural worker currently based in Nairobi. He is interested in the potential of creative networks and collaboration, and developing new opportunities and engagement for artists and audiences.

Currently, Robert is a Consultant for Strathmore Business School and Strathmore University on projects that work with business ventures in the creative field. 

Between 2020-2022, Robert was a consultant and facilitator for the ArtXchange Project for the GoDown Arts Centre. The GoDown Arts Centre was one of the consortium partners and the lead training partner for the European Union funded Cultural Project that brought together cultural organizations from Europe (Italy and Sweden) and Africa (Kenya and Somalia). The project sought to improve the livelihoods of artists in Kenya and Somalia/Somaliland and also offer mobility/connecting opportunities between Europe and Africa.

Between 2014-16, Robert was an the Local Project Manager for an East African Cultural Programme funded by the European Union called the Structural Support for the Cultural Sectors in Kenya and Tanzania. 

And in 2014, Robert was an Associate Project Manager at Strathmore Law School 

Robert studied Political Science and Economics at Nairobi University, where he obtained a B. Arts (Political Science and Economics) degree.

Robert is also the editor for NairobiNow, an influential blog that lists arts and cultural events taking place in and out of Nairobi.
